            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView18"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Preheat the Oven:

Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).
Prepare the Corn:

If using fresh corn, remove the kernels from the cobs. If using frozen corn, thaw it according to package instructions.
Make the Cream Sauce:

In a saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat. Stir in the flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 1-2 minutes to make a roux.
Add Milk and Seasonings:

Gradually whisk in the milk to the roux, ensuring there are no lumps. Add sugar, salt, and black pepper. Cook the sauce until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Temper the Eggs:

In a separate bowl, beat the eggs. Gradually whisk a small amount of the hot cream sauce into the beaten eggs to temper them. Then, slowly whisk the tempered eggs back into the saucepan with the rest of the sauce.
Combine with Corn:

Stir in the corn kernels and shredded cheddar cheese (if using) into the cream sauce until well combined.
Transfer to Baking Dish:

Pour the corn mixture into a greased baking dish, spreading it out evenly.
Top with Breadcrumbs:

Sprinkle breadcrumbs evenly over the top of the corn mixture.
Bake:

Bake in the preheated oven for approximately 30-35 minutes or until the top is golden brown, and the center is set.
Garnish and Serve:

Remove from the oven, garnish with chopped fresh parsley if desired, and let it cool for a few minutes before serving."
